        "title": "float used in pixels measurements",
        "body": "```css\r\n@alt-border-width: 1.25px;\r\n```\r\n\r\nKnowing a pixel is the smallest unit in CSS, i.e. the smallest visible part of a screen (each dot of a screen is a pixel), it makes absolutely no sense to give decimals to pixels measure except for making size calculations harder and imprecise.\r\n\r\nBecause when you see decimals on measurements in pixels it is because they re the result of a calculation but in no way they should be a CSS rule.\r\n\r\nSo you have to remove all the pixels decimals you've added. And I wonder how you could see the difference between 1 and 1.25 except if you were zoomed, which would be VERY VERY BAD for writing CSS...",
